The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kollam, Nov. 27 (PTI): A man allegedly forced his wife to abandon her two-year-old daughter in a shed swarming with ants in Keralas Meeyannur village.           
	Police have taken the man into custody while the girl, his stepdaughter, receives treatment at hospital. The mother has been entrusted to a home for destitute women, and the baby girl to the child welfare council.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): The Cochin University of Science and Technology has ordered a probe into the disfigurement of a grass mermaid on its campus, which had triggered protests from some womens groups in Kerala. Pro vice-chancellor Godfrey Luis will submit the results of the probe in a week.                  
	Kochi (PTI): A fast track court has upheld a former vice-chancellors five-year prison term for harassing his daughter-in-law for dowry. The family of Sethupathy Ramalingam had allegedly demanded jewellery, cars and cash from his daughter-in-law Sangeetha.                   
	Bangalore (PTI): Karnataka Lokayukta Santosh Hegde has issued a notice to chief minister B.S. Yeddyurappa regarding the controversial denotification of land after it found a prima facie case following a complaint by Janata Dal (Secular).          
	Fake refund          
	New Delhi (PTI): A man has been arrested after allegedly trying to deposit fake income-tax refund cheques for Rs 47 lakh. Sources in the income-tax department said a local gang had been claiming huge sums of bogus tax refunds.                  
	Ghaziabad (PTI): Unidentified people have demanded Rs 10 lakh from an official of the district bar association. Superintendent of police A.K. Vijeta has assured advocate Kiran Sharma of police protection and a probe into the incident on Thursday. Sharma was threatened with dire consequences if she did not pay the sum.                                                                                                                                              
